{% doc %}
# Flexible Grid Layout Block

## Overview
A versatile grid layout block for card-based content displays. Perfect for showcasing features, products, or services.

## Features
- **Flexible Layout Options**: 1–4 columns, 2-row layouts
- **Responsive Design**: Separate mobile and desktop layouts
- **Content Management**: Up to 8 individual content items
- **Theme Styling**: Inherits colors and typography from the active color scheme and type scale
- **Image Support**: Optional images with placeholder fallbacks
- **Interactive Elements**: Optional call-to-action buttons
- **Width Control**: Fit (page width) or Fill (full width)

## Usage
Add this block to any section. Configure the layout, add content to items, and the block will style itself using the theme’s color scheme and typography.

## Content Structure
Each grid item can contain:
- **Image** (optional)
- **Heading** (theme heading styles)
- **Description text** (theme body style)
- **Call-to-action button** (optional)

## Layout Options

### Width
- **Fit**: Constrains to the theme page width with side padding
- **Fill**: Spans the full browser width

### Desktop Layouts
- 1, 2, 3 (default), or 4 columns
- 2 rows × 2 columns, or 2 rows × 3 columns

### Mobile Layouts
- 1 column

## Styling
- **Colors**: Inherits from the section’s color scheme (no per-block color pickers)
- **Typography**: Uses theme heading and body styles (no per-block typography pickers)
- **Items**: Controls for padding, corner radius, border width, optional shadow, min height, and alignment
- **Buttons**: Uses theme primary button styles; supports corner radius

## Responsive Behavior
- Desktop uses selected desktop layout
- Tablet (≤1024px): 4-column layout collapses to 2 columns
- Mobile (≤768px): Uses selected mobile layout and reduced gaps
- Small mobile (≤480px): Forces single column

## Technical Notes
- Uses CSS Grid for layout and flexbox for item content alignment
- Derives colors from `color-<scheme>` CSS variables
- Generates unique CSS classes using block ID to prevent conflicts

